From 3b3c897b8bf65d97057b759ea0e39a6ff91a8f9f Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: Srinivas Pitla <spitla@qti.qualcomm.com>
Date: Fri, 4 Jul 2025 14:09:56 -0700
Subject: [PATCH 1/2] [PATCH 1/2] UPSTREAM: PROTOCOL: hostapd: Add AAL feature
 support

The AAL feature indicates MLO stations to use max active
links for association. The max active links information
is shared in Ext MLD CAP of Common Info field of Basic
ML IE in beacon and broadcast probe response frames.

This feature can be enabled and disabled dynamically.
It also allows user to update max active links runtime.

This change would also indicate driver about ML Max
recommeneded links on start_ap and update_ap.

This is defined as per IEEE P802.11be/D7.0 spec 9.4.2.322.2.3 Common
Info field of the Basic Multi-Link element.

Signed-off-by: Srinivas Pitla <spitla@qti.qualcomm.com>
